    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Synthetic arsenic disulfide first made in the 18th century as the counterpart to natural realgar. The synthetic variety was purer and less expensive, but is no longer used because of its toxicity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種合成的二硫化砷，首度製造於西元十八世紀，相對應的天然生成物即為雄黃。此合成顏料比天然雄黃的質地更純、價格也較低，但因具毒性，現已不再使用。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Synthetisch arseendisulfide dat voor het eerst werd gemaakt in de 18e eeuw als tegenhanger van natuurlijk realgar. De synthetische variant was zuiverder en minder duur, maar wordt niet meer gebruikt vanwege de toxiciteit.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
